---
// /for-vets/ — vertical lander for independent veterinary clinics across North America (Phase 5, 2026-05-04)
// Persona language sourced from OVMA / AVMA / Today's Veterinary Business / vet practice-management forums.
// Lead feature per ICP research: AI Voice Receptionist + Missed-Call-Text-Back ("the bleeding wound").
// Avoid SaaS jargon. Use industry terms: recall, lapsed clients, wellness plans, CSR, PIMS, AVImark, Cornerstone.

import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="For independent vet clinics &mdash; Stop losing clients to voicemail"
  description="AI customer lifecycle for independent veterinary clinics across Canada and the United States. Catch after-hours calls, run recall on autopilot, drown out bad reviews. Wraps around AVImark, Cornerstone, ezyVet, Vetspire. CVO/AVMA advertising rules respected. A service of Agni Consulting."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="ai-hero">
    <p class="ai-eyebrow">FOR INDEPENDENT VET CLINICS</p>
    <h1>Your front desk goes home at 6.<br>We don&rsquo;t.</h1>
    <p class="ai-lead">
      Independent vet clinics miss 24&ndash;28% of inbound calls during peak hours &mdash; and 85% of those callers don&rsquo;t call back. Your last 18 months of lapsed clients are sitting in AVImark or Cornerstone, never reached out to. Your Google reviews are 4.6 stars and 142; the corporate clinic four blocks away is at 4.7 with 600. None of it is your fault. The medicine has to come first.
    </p>
    <p class="ai-lead" style="font-weight:600;color:var(--tx);">
      We run the whole client lifecycle for you. After-hours call rescue, recall on autopilot, reactivation, review automation, win-back. Done-for-you, by operators &mdash; not an agency, not a SaaS dashboard.
    </p>
    <div class="ai-cta-row">
      <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a free Growth Audit &rarr;</a>
      <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/engagements/">Engagement shapes</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The leaks (pain bullets) -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow">If any of these sound familiar</p>
      <h2>This is what a leaky clinic looks like.</h2>
      <ul class="ai-painlist" style="font-size:17px;margin-top:24px;">
        <li>"The phones never stop ringing — but we still missed 47 calls last week."</li>
        <li>"Our front desk turned over again. We're back to square one on phone scripts and recall."</li>
        <li>"I know we have 3,000 clients who haven't been in for 18 months. We've never reached out to a single one."</li>
        <li>"Our wellness plan attach rate is in the toilet. The CSR forgets to pitch it half the time."</li>
        <li>"Reviews? Yeah, the receptionist was supposed to text every client a link. That stopped 2 months in."</li>
        <li>"The new associate vet has 30% open capacity and we don't know how to fill it."</li>
        <li>"VCA / VetStrategy keeps emailing me about acquisition. I don't want to sell. I'm just tired."</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top:32px;color:var(--tx-soft);font-size:16px;">
        None of these are your fault. Running an independent practice in 2026 means doing the medicine, the team, the front desk, the billing, the marketing, and the reviews — and the medicine has to come first. Everything else gets the leftovers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we do -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow" style="text-align:center;">What we run for you</p>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:32px;">Five systems. One platform. Wraps around your existing PIMS.</h2>
      <div class="ai-grid-2">

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>1. AI receptionist + missed-call-text-back</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">An AI receptionist answers every call you can't. Books an appointment when it can, sends a text when it can't. Every missed call gets a personalized SMS within 60 seconds: "Hi — sorry we missed you, here's our online booking link, want a callback?"</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>After-hours, weekends, lunch — covered</li>
            <li>Trained on YOUR services, hours, fee schedule</li>
            <li>Hands off to a human when needed</li>
            <li>Every call logged, transcribed, summarized in your dashboard</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>2. Recall &amp; reactivation on autopilot</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">Pulls your AVImark / Cornerstone / ezyVet client list. Identifies pets due for vaccines, dentals, wellness exams, lapsed clients (90+ days, 180+ days, 1 year+). Sends the right SMS at the right interval. Books appointments straight into your PIMS calendar.</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Vaccine + preventive recall sequences</li>
            <li>Lapsed-client win-back (1 yr+ inactive)</li>
            <li>Wellness plan re-pitch automation</li>
            <li>Two-way SMS — clients reply, your CSR sees it</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>3. Review automation (CVO-compliant)</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">Automatic SMS review request 1 hour after every visit. CVO advertising rules respected — no incentivization, no scripted testimonials, plain ask. Negative feedback routes to your inbox first. Average clinic adds 30+ Google reviews in the first 90 days.</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Google + Facebook reviews</li>
            <li>Negative feedback intercepted to private inbox</li>
            <li>CVO-compliant copy (we know the rules)</li>
            <li>Review reply automation with your tone</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>4. Appointment reminders that stick</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">SMS reminders at 7 days, 24 hours, 2 hours. Auto-rebook on cancellation. Surgery prep instructions sent automatically. Clinics report 38–50% no-show reduction in month one.</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Multi-touch SMS reminder sequence</li>
            <li>Auto-rebook on cancellation</li>
            <li>Surgery / fasting prep instructions</li>
            <li>Two-way confirm / reschedule</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card">
          <h3>5. Front-desk overflow + dashboard</h3>
          <p style="margin-bottom:16px;">Your CSR sees one inbox: SMS, missed calls, reviews, recall replies. Owner sees one dashboard: bookings recovered, reviews added, recall revenue, lapsed clients re-engaged. Monthly report PDF for the practice meeting.</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Unified team inbox (SMS / calls / reviews)</li>
            <li>Owner dashboard with monthly KPIs</li>
            <li>PIMS sync for AVImark / Cornerstone / ezyVet / Vetspire</li>
            <li>End-of-month PDF for the practice meeting</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="ai-card" style="border-color:var(--accent);background:var(--accent-soft);">
          <h3 style="color:var(--accent);">Built around your PIMS, not replacing it.</h3>
          <p>You will not switch software. You will not retrain your team. We integrate as a layer on top — the front desk still uses AVImark / Cornerstone / ezyVet exactly the way they do today. Our system fills the gaps.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ROI calculator -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap">
      <div class="ai-calc">
        <p class="ai-eyebrow">Quick math</p>
        <h3>What's a missed call actually costing you?</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);margin-bottom:0;">Plug in your numbers. We won&rsquo;t store this. The defaults are AVMA industry averages for an independent North American clinic.</p>
        <div class="ai-calc-grid">
          <div class="ai-calc-field">
            <label>Calls received per week</label>
            <input type="number" id="calls-week" value="120" min="0" />
          </div>
          <div class="ai-calc-field">
            <label>% of calls missed</label>
            <input type="number" id="miss-pct" value="30" min="0" max="100" />
          </div>
          <div class="ai-calc-field">
            <label>% of missed callers who become a new client</label>
            <input type="number" id="conv-pct" value="20" min="0" max="100" />
          </div>
          <div class="ai-calc-field">
            <label>Avg lifetime value of a new client ($)</label>
            <input type="number" id="ltv" value="2000" min="0" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-calc-output">
          <p>You're losing approximately:</p>
          <div class="ai-calc-big" id="calc-loss">$374,400 / yr</div>
          <p style="margin:8px 0 0;font-size:14px;">…to voicemail. We typically recover 60–80% of that in the first 6 months.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ai-cta-row" style="justify-content:flex-start;margin-top:24px;">
          <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a free audit →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Engagement shapes -->
  <section class="ai-section">
    <div class="ai-wrap">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow" style="text-align:center;">Engagement shapes</p>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:8px;">Three shapes. Audit first. No long contracts.</h2>
      <p style="text-align:center;color:var(--tx-soft);margin-bottom:32px;max-width:640px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
        Engagements typically range from low-four-figures to mid-four-figures monthly (USD), scoped to your size and the systems we run for you. We share the specific number on the audit call once we&rsquo;ve seen what fits.
      </p>
      <div class="ai-tiers">

        <article class="ai-tier">
          <h3>1. Free Growth Audit</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Diagnose, free</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price" style="font-size:24px;">Free</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">30 min &middot; one-page leak report in 24 hrs</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Live walk-through of your AVImark / Cornerstone / ezyVet / Vetspire</li>
            <li>Phone log + missed-call analysis</li>
            <li>Google profile + review audit</li>
            <li>One-page leak report ranked by recoverable revenue</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">Book audit &rarr;</a>
        </article>

        <article class="ai-tier ai-tier-featured">
          <h3>2. Pilot</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Most clinics start here</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price" style="font-size:24px;">60 days, fixed scope</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">See dollar impact before any monthly commitment</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Highest-leverage system from leak report (usually missed-call recovery + review automation)</li>
            <li>Twilio number + AI receptionist trained on your services</li>
            <li>PIMS integration live in 7&ndash;14 days</li>
            <li>Weekly check-in for 60 days</li>
            <li>End-of-pilot dollar-impact report</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">Book audit &rarr;</a>
        </article>

        <article class="ai-tier">
          <h3>3. Run-It</h3>
          <p class="ai-tier-tagline">Done-for-you, end-to-end</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price" style="font-size:24px;">Monthly retainer</p>
          <p class="ai-tier-price-sub">Cancel any time after first 90 days</p>
          <ul class="ai-checklist">
            <li>Full lifecycle: missed-call rescue, recall, reactivation, reviews, lead response, win-back</li>
            <li>AI voice receptionist 24/7</li>
            <li>Custom n8n integrations (your specific PIMS quirks)</li>
            <li>Dedicated ops contact, weekly check-in</li>
            <li>Quarterly strategy session with Aman</li>
          </ul>
          <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;">Book audit &rarr;</a>
        </article>

      </div>
      <p style="text-align:center;color:var(--tx-soft);margin-top:24px;font-size:14px;">CVO and AVMA advertising rules respected. HIPAA / PIPEDA-aware where required. Full pricing on the audit call. No multi-year contracts.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trust / about hint -->
  <section class="ai-section-tight">
    <div class="ai-wrap ai-narrow" style="text-align:center;">
      <p class="ai-eyebrow">Why us</p>
      <h2>Built around your stack. By operators.</h2>
      <p style="color:var(--tx-soft);margin-top:16px;line-height:1.7;">
        Agni AI Store is a service of <a href="https://shopagni.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--accent);">Agni Consulting</a> &mdash; a marketing-ops practice that&rsquo;s spent the last decade running this exact stack inside Series-A and Series-B B2B SaaS. We integrate with AVImark, Cornerstone, ezyVet, Vetspire, Covetrus Pulse, and PetDesk. We respect CVO and AVMA advertising rules. We serve independent vet clinics across Canada and the United States from our base in Toronto.
      </p>
      <div class="ai-cta-row" style="margin-top:28px;">
        <a class="ai-btn" href="https://calendly.com/aman-shopagni" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a 30-min audit &rarr;</a>
        <a class="ai-btn-ghost" href="/about/">About Aman</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script is:inline>
  // ROI calculator — pure client-side, no server.
  (function () {
    const callsEl = document.getElementById('calls-week');
    const missEl = document.getElementById('miss-pct');
    const convEl = document.getElementById('conv-pct');
    const ltvEl = document.getElementById('ltv');
    const out = document.getElementById('calc-loss');
    if (!callsEl) return;

    function fmt(n) {
      return '$' + Math.round(n).toLocaleString('en-CA') + ' / yr';
    }

    function recalc() {
      const calls = parseFloat(callsEl.value) || 0;
      const missPct = (parseFloat(missEl.value) || 0) / 100;
      const convPct = (parseFloat(convEl.value) || 0) / 100;
      const ltv = parseFloat(ltvEl.value) || 0;
      const annualLoss = calls * 52 * missPct * convPct * ltv;
      out.textContent = fmt(annualLoss);
    }

    [callsEl, missEl, convEl, ltvEl].forEach((el) => el.addEventListener('input', recalc));
    recalc();
  })();
</script>
